# npm publish is deferred (no NPM_TOKEN; see release.yml). When it lands, the
# distribution strategy is NOT to ship the per-platform compiled binaries
# inside this one tarball. The plan (per the distribution-and-packaging audit,
# 2026-05-31) is the esbuild/swc pattern: a thin launcher package + per-platform
# `optionalDependencies` that each carry one `dist/am-<os>-<arch>` binary. So
# `dist/` is intentionally excluded here, and `package.json` "files" no longer
# lists it — the two files agreed to disagree before, which silently dropped
# dist from the publish set. Until that strategy is built, npm ships only the
# source + bin/ launchers (which fall back to `bun run src/cli.ts`).
dist/

test/
docs/
research/
ADRs/
scripts/
.github/
.claude/
.overstory/
wrangler.toml
biome.json
tsconfig.json
*.test.ts
